<br>
But, Palimax, I don't think your reason is the true reason you outfit warriors first.  Obviously warriors are the tanks in the upper end game and you must have well equipped tanks to handle mobs such as Vindi and Velks.  Nevertheless, the underlying reason you outfit warriors first is that you (as a guild) are not willing to wait until the warrior is outfitted normally with everyone else before advancing to the next step.<br>
<br>
Essentially the real reason to outfit warriors first is impatience.  You CAN  (in a theoretical scenario) have a true random loot structure and any other distributed type of loot structure and eventually work your way up the food chain.  It will take much longer of course as the lack of equipment on the MT will be the limiting factor.  So, for something that might take 6 months before a guild is ready for Vindi (e.g. before the MT is outfitted under your MT gets first structure), it may take 2-3 years before the MT is outfitted and ready for Vindi under a different structure. <br>
<br>
Human nature as it is, however, it is dubious whether people would stick around for the extra time it takes to outfit the MT (this is of course the impatience).  Moreover, you have the interplay of the 6 month scenario allowing no other tanks access to any loot (and thus possible disgruntled members) whereas under the 2-3 year scenario pretty much everyone progresses from an equipment standpoint at the same pace. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uwilrowe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wilrowe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/16/02 5:46:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=804.topic&index=263>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Things you do after leaving a guild...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> i am assuming it is a dot that he casted<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
