<br>
I wanted to break this quote up for two responses, but I didn't want anything to get out of context.<br>
<br>
Vision, as a guild, spends 1 or 2 raid sessions a week working soley on equipping the guild as a whole.  Even for those armor raids to be successful, it's important that Allamar* to be as well dressed as possible; so it's not so much so that we can go do Velkator or Vindicator.  We use a MA strategy while getting armor as well.<br>
<br>
I'm also not sure that it's a matter of &quot;next step&quot; or &quot;willing to wait.&quot;  We don't have an incremental plan for our targets.  There's a 10,000ft overview for what we'd like to acomplish as a guild on the short term (kill Dozekar, finish more VP keys) and there's things we want to do long term (see ST someday), but it's not a formula.<br>
<br>
Farm Kael and PoG until you have the gear for ToV.  Farm ToV until you have the gear for Vindicator.  Kill Vindicator until you're good enough for NToV.  Kill NToV until you can take on the Luclin Bosses.  Blah blah blah.<br>
<br>
It's just a matter of what happens.<br>
<br>
We didn't outfit Allamar first because we're lazy or impatient.  We outfitted Allamar first because at the time we did it, it made the most sense to help us with our short term goals.  Also, by the time Allamar's finishing pieces dropped, we already had other tanks in near-full armor, and since then we've got half a dozen or so plate wearers that are &quot;done&quot; with ToV/SS armor (including clerics).<br>
<br>
I also thing &quot;outfitted normally&quot; has a lot to do with your overall perception of normality.  I'm <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> one of</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the best dressed casters in our guild.  I don't have anything freakishy amazing like those Vulak killers over in that big guild; but I do have pretty nice gear relative to Vision's size and power.  To us, &quot;outfitted normally&quot; means that we all have about the same gear porportionally to our tenure, level and participation, except for a handful of items distributed to key players for key guild functions.  Beyond outfitting a few key tanks, distribution is pretty spread out on items   ...and since we have people pass down old &quot;inferior&quot; items, when we put a RBB on Allamar this last week, we put an RBG on another melee.  Similarly, the Vision epic-weapon count is now 58, which puts us at over half**.<br>
<br>
I agree that, if a million pieces of armor were to drop, and they were to be randomed amongst 100 people, you'd all get about 10,000 pieces -- and whatever minor fluctuations you had would be so trivial that it's not worth mentioning.  Now if only uilds got a million pieces of armor to distribute...  When you have 100 pieces to distribute to 100 people, under a random system, how many people have 2 and 3 before someone gets a single piece?<br>
<br>
Play a special game of Keno where after picking a ball they immediately put it back in the hopper.  How many times, on average, do you think they have to pick a ball before EVERY spot on the page is covered?  That's the downside (as we see it) to a random system.  There's no excuse to give three items to #5 before #4 gets any.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> [*I pick on Allamar a lot, but it's because he's a good guy.  I use him in every example I ever use because, as far as I know, not a single person on the server has a bad thing to say about him.  We have several other warlords.  At least one has more AC and HP than Allamar does, and all but one of them is in full or near-full Skyshrine.]</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
